cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CR

This paper is about video streaming over HTTP/2, which is a multimedia technology. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the server push mechanism and the unfairness problem in adaptive streaming, which are related to network protocols and algorithms. Hence, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also likely sub-categories. The proposed framework aims to ensure fairness and improve the streaming experience, which involves optimization and performance evaluation. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also possible sub-categories.
